isagreed over what these traditions were and how to transform them. They make it clear that nationalism was a powerful motivating force in the modern development of these countries, but they stress that a wide variety of nationalisms emerged and collided in the dramatic history of modern Asia.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aHISTORY / Asia / General.2bisacsh1 aCohen, Warren I., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEckert, Carter J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGaron, Sheldon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoldman, Merle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoldman, Merle, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGordon, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGordon, Andrew, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHowell, David L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKirby, William C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNathan, Andrew J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRankin, Mary Backus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchoppa, R. Keith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYoung, Ernest P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674273092zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674273092423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674273092/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA